></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.allwords.com/word-mother.html">"Definition from"</a>. Allwords.com. 2007-09-14<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2011-11-04</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Definition+from&amp;rft.pub=Allwords.com&amp;rft.date=2007-09-14&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.allwords.com%2Fword-mother.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AParent" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Bromham, David (1990). <i>Philosophical Ethics in Reproductive Medicine</i>. p.&#160;57.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Philosophical+Ethics+in+Reproductive+Medicine&amp;rft.pages=57&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.aulast=Bromham&amp;rft.aufirst=David&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AParent" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.thefreedictionary.com/father">"TheFreeDictionary"</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2014-10-07</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=TheFreeDictionary&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thefreedictionary.com%2Ffather&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A